heir mutual interdependence. It contributes new, ground-breaking insights into the questions of literalness, semantics-pragmatics interface, automatic (default) retrieval and contextual pragmatic enrichment, modelling of discourse processing, lexical pragmatics, and other related issues.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCognition. 0aDiscourse analysisxSocial aspects. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxPhonology. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLinguistic Defaults.  aSalience.  aSemantic/Pragmatic Interface.  aUtterance Processing.1 aAllan, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllan, Keith, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGernsbacher, Morton Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiora, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaugh, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaszczolt, Kasia M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaszczolt, Kasia M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKapogianni, Eleni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKecskes, Istvan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeleg, Orna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPitts, Alyson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Sem